parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Transmission Safety Interlock Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and transmission safety interlock can cause the vehicle to roll forward or backward, even when the driver has removed the key from the ignition, leading to accidents and property damage.
symptoms: The key can be removed from the ignition switch without the gear being in the park position
allowing the vehicle to roll forward or backward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, which can lead to engine damage, overheating, and potentially, engine fires.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the valve cover
engine shakes and bucks when putting in reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leak and Related Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially, engine fires. Related issues such as faulty oil sending units, thermostat failure, and engine shaking can further compromise vehicle safety and performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failures, including fuel pump failure, fuel hose failure, and oxygen sensor failure, can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially, engine fires.
Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially, harm occupants.
